The Strandline Compact is Mafdet's governing framework, a mutual-obligation agreement between the city's three operational blocs forged during the Fracture Era.
When inland authority collapsed and Mafdet had to build its own governance from scratch, the Compact formalized the tripartite power structure that had been developing informally since the Harbor Foundation era.
The three blocs are: the Harbor Wardens (quay security, berthing law, harbor chain), the Ledger Houses (cargo certification, debt instruments), and the Sand-Sea Carters' Guild (overland linkage through Saltglass Reach).
The Compact's constitutional principle is interdependence: no bloc can dominate because any two can veto the third.
Harbor Wardens control physical access to the quay and set berthing priority — without their cooperation no cargo moves.
Ledger Houses control cargo certification and debt instruments — without their seals no cargo has recognized provenance.
The Sand-Sea Carters' Guild controls the overland linkage connecting Mafdet to the inland trade network — without the Guild's routes, maritime goods cannot reach inland markets and inland goods cannot reach the port.
The Compact's governing maxim is "harbor first, dual attestation, swift judgment" — priorities ranked in that order when conflicts arise.
The Shrine of the First Claw is not formally a Compact bloc but functions as the Compact's judicial enforcement mechanism, with all three blocs respecting Shrine verdicts.
The Compact was negotiated when the coastal settlement's early factions realized that unilateral control by any one party would collapse the system that supported all three.
Unlike oasis settlements that inherited Keeper institutional frameworks, Mafdet invented its Compact from caravan logistics, harbor engineering, and the guardian cult's trust-enforcement tradition.

